        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 3:13PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 313 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Tierra Monte, or 8 miles south of Mora, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mora, Ledoux, Tierra Monte, Morphy Lake State Park, Cleveland, La
Cueva, Gascon, South Carmen, Monte Aplanado and Rociada.

This includes the following highways...
State Road 94 between Mile Markers 5 and 18.
State Road 518 between Mile Markers 19 and 35.
State Road 283 near Mile Marker 13.
State Road 276 between Mile Markers 0 and 5.
State Road 266 near Mile Marker 6.
State Road 434 between Mile Markers 0 and 3.
State Road 105 between Mile Markers 0 and 8.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Accumulations of small hail on roads can create very slick and
hazardous driving conditions.</instruction>
